This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it deals with Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs). It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses reducing parameterization to improve computational efficiency. Additionally, it could be classified under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with natural language processing using RNNs. The paper's focus on achieving comparable validation accuracy while reducing computational costs also makes it relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's potential applications in computer vision make it relevant to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
